  "body": "There are several places the code where we call [CombinedChainDataClient.getStateAtSlot](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/b2e25bcf233494a50789a80e314509292f0ed54d/storage/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/storage/CombinedChainDataClient.java#L176) assuming a state will be returned even if the slot is skipped.  For example, the [call to get committee assignments](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/405ad2d45457bb1d79d17b82904639e69456a900/storage/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/storage/CombinedChainDataClient.java#L223) invoked from the [/beacon/committees handler](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/b2e25bcf233494a50789a80e314509292f0ed54d/data/beaconrestapi/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/beaconrestapi/handlers/beacon/GetCommittees.java#L77), asks for the state at some epoch boundary.  If there is no block proposed on this epoch boundary, we will not retrieve a state because both calls [to get historical state](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/405ad2d45457bb1d79d17b82904639e69456a900/storage/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/storage/CombinedChainDataClient.java#L168) and calls [to get recent state](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/405ad2d45457bb1d79d17b82904639e69456a900/storage/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/storage/CombinedChainDataClient.java#L176) only return state that corresponds to a block proposed at the exact slot requested.  \n\nOne suggestion to test these cases would be to migrate our [Rest API integration tests to use a real data-backed ChainStorageClient](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/b2e25bcf233494a50789a80e314509292f0ed54d/data/beaconrestapi/src/integration-test/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/beaconrestapi/AbstractBeaconRestAPIIntegrationTest.java#L50) with data setup via [BeaconChainTestUtil](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/master/ethereum/statetransition/src/testFixtures/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/statetransition/BeaconChainUtil.java#L43).  With this util, we can produce a series of blocks, skipping various slots strategically for testing.  ",
